law.text:
The board may issue a license as a massage therapist to an applicant who:
Is eighteen (18) years of age or older;
Has paid the application fee and other fees required by the board;
Is a person of good moral character;
Has successfully completed a course of study consisting of a minimum of six hundred (600) hours of supervised instruction in a massage therapy training program approved by the board; and
Has successfully passed an examination administered by the National Certification Board for Therapeutic Massage and Bodywork or a certifying agency that has been approved by the National Commission for Certifying Agencies, or other examinations approved by the board.
